White sneakers are very stylish and versatile shoes. However, some people may shy away from getting a pair because they wonder how they will ever get them clean. Here are easy tips to get your white canvas sneakers clean without turning them yellow. 1. Wash the shoes first. Run water over the dirty shoes and rinse to remove excess dirt like mud or vegetation that you may have picked up under the shoes. 2.Â Mix water with detergent of your choice and bleach Remove the laces from your white canvas shoes then soak them overnight in the mixture. 3. Scrub scrub scrub Once nicely soaked, use a scrub brush to scrub your shoes thoroughly without missing a spot. Scrub the shoelaces as well. 4. Rinse. Rinse the shoes with clean water severally to remove any soap that may cause a stain after the shoes dry. 5. Cover before drying. Put a layer of tissue paper all around the shoe to help absorb any remaining stains. Dry the shoes in the sun. If you did not know about this hack, now you know.